definitions.definition: The global, decentralized network of computers which communicate with one another using the Internet protocol suite , which now forms a vital part of global communication, content sharing, and information exchange systems.
( by extension , informal ) The global community of individuals communicating via the Internet.

Alternative letter-case form of Internet ( “ the specific internet consisting of a global network of computers that communicate using Internet Protocol (IP) and that use Border Gateway Protocol (BGP) to identify the best paths to route those communications ” ) .
Alternative letter-case form of Internet ( “ global community of individuals communicating via the Internet ” ) .
examples: As soon as the trailer was released, the internet went nuts.
